nodes.bodyText:
@Electroid I agree with @Pablete1234. It is rather excessive for magic numbers, but personally I feel it’s more organized and understandable for new contributors who may want to adjust them later on.
If you dislike them all at the top of the file, I can move each respective pair above the event they’re related to like:
...
private static final int CORE_LEAK_COUNT = 8;
private static final double CORE_LEAK_RADIUS = 1.5;

 @EventHandler(priority = EventPriority.MONITOR)
   public void onCoreLeak(final CoreLeakEvent event) {
     if (GOALS_ENABLED && event.getCore().isVisible()) {
       this.spawnFireworkDisplay(
           event.getMatch().getWorld(),
           event.getCore().getCasingRegion(),
           event.getCore().getColor(),
           CORE_LEAK_COUNT,
           CORE_LEAK_RADIUS,
           ROCKET_POWER);
     }
   }

